A vintage-style illustration of an antique wooden card catalog cabinet with dozens of small drawers, each drawer pulled out at different angles revealing colorful paper tags spilling out and floating through the air like confetti. The tags are various saturated colors - amber, teal, coral, and sage - creating organic flowing patterns as they cascade and interweave above the cabinet. Warm sepia undertones with aged paper texture overlay the entire scene. Soft golden light streams from an unseen window, casting long shadows. The floating tags form natural clusters and intersections mid-air, some overlapping to create new color combinations where they meet. Dust motes visible in the light beams. Weathered brass drawer pulls catch highlights. Rich mahogany wood grain visible on the cabinet surface.
